MODE

Usage: ^gMODE
       MODE <SS/SA/BF>
       MODE FA <amount of rounds>^n

This command is used both to display the firing modes your
currently wielded weapon has and to set the firing mode. 
The amount of rounds fired in fully automatic mode must be
between 3 and 10.

Firing Modes Are:
SS	- Single Shot
SA	- Semi-Automatic
BF	- Burst Fire
FA	- Fully Automatic

^WSee Also: RECOIL^n
